quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  67,27,"But, when they shall see it close at hand, the faces of the disbelievers will turn black with gloom, and it will be said to them: \"This is which you were calling for"
  67,28,"Further say: \"Have you ever considered that even if Allah destroys me as well as those with me or bestows His mercy on us; who will save the disbelievers from a painful punishment"
  67,29,"Say: \"He is the Compassionate: in Him we have believed, and in Him we have put our trust. Soon you will find out, which one of us is in the manifest error"
  67,30,"Say: \"Have you ever considered that if all the water you have, sink down in the ground, who is it, that will bring you the clear-flowing water"
  68,1,Nun. By the pen and what they write
  68,2,By the grace of your Lord you are not a madman
  68,3,and you shall have a never ending reward
  68,4,You are of the highest noble character
  68,5,Soon you will see - as they will see
  68,6,which of you is afflicted with madness
  68,7,"Surely it is your Lord Who knows those who have strayed from His Way, as He knows best those who are rightly guided"
  68,8,So do not yield to the unbelievers
  68,9,"They desire you to compromise a little, so they too would compromise"
  68,10,Neither yield to any mean oath-monger
  68,11,mischief making slanderer
  68,12,"opponent of good, transgressor"
  68,13,"wicked oppressor, and above all, ignoble by birth"
  68,14,though he be possessing wealth and children
  68,15,"When Our revelations are recited to him , he says: \"They are nothing but the tales of the ancients"